  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/DocumentRowMenu.tsx` exists and exports a `DocumentRowMenu` React component with props `{ document: IDocumentRowMenuTarget, onAction: (action: DocumentRowAction) =&gt; void, disabledActions?: DocumentRowAction[] }`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`IDocumentRowMenuTarget` and `DocumentRowAction` types are exported from `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/types/DocumentRowMenu.ts`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All 12 leaf actions render in FR-DOC-01 order with 2 dividers (after `findSimilar` and after `openRecord`); clicking each menu item invokes `onAction` with the matching action key.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Trigger button uses `appearance="subtle"`, `size="small"`, and icon `MoreVertical20Regular`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Trigger button's `onClick` calls `stopPropagation` BEFORE the menu opens — verified by mounting the component inside a parent `div` with its own `onClick` spy and confirming the parent spy is NOT called when the trigger is clicked.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`disabledActions` removes the specified actions from the rendered menu; dividers are still placed correctly between remaining groups.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Zero hardcoded hex/rgb (grep verifiable); Fluent v9 tokens used throughout.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Component renders correctly in both `webLightTheme` and `webDarkTheme`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No React 18+ exclusive APIs; `npm run build:prod` succeeds in `@spaarke/ui-components` and in both PCFs.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Portal gotcha mitigation per `.claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-portal-gotcha.md` is applied.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`code-review` + `adr-check` skills pass with no unresolved findings.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">TASK-INDEX.md shows task 011 as ✅ completed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Trigger stopPropagation — row click does not fire">
      <steps>
        <step>Mount `&lt;div onClick={parentSpy}&gt;&lt;DocumentRowMenu ... /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;` in a test harness.</step>
        <step>Click the menu trigger button (the 3-dot button).</step>
        <step>Assert `parentSpy` was NOT called.</step>
        <step>Assert the menu opens correctly.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Trigger swallows propagation; parent onClick does not fire; menu opens.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="13-item structure renders in exact FR-DOC-01 order">
      <steps>
        <step>Mount `DocumentRowMenu` with no `disabledActions`.</step>
        <step>Open the menu.</step>
        <step>Walk the rendered menu nodes in DOM order; assert the sequence: Preview, AI summary, Open file, Find similar, divider, Download, Copy link, Email, Open record, divider, Toggle workspace, Pin to top, Rename, Delete.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>All 12 leaf items in correct order, 2 dividers placed exactly after `findSimilar` and after `openRecord`.</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="disabledActions hides items + preserves divider placement">
      <steps>
        <step>Mount `DocumentRowMenu` with `disabledActions={['delete', 'rename']}`.</step>
        <step>Open menu; assert Delete and Rename are NOT in DOM.</step>
        <step>Mount again with `disabledActions={['download', 'copyLink', 'email', 'openRecord']}` (entire middle group).</step>
        <step>Assert the first divider remains (between group 1 and group 3) and no empty group is rendered.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Hidden items disappear; remaining menu structure is still well-formed (no orphaned dividers, no empty groups).</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="Dark mode rendering + axe pass">
      <steps>
        <step>Mount inside FluentProvider with `webDarkTheme`; open menu.</step>
        <step>Run axe-core scan on the entire menu tree.</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>Zero WCAG 2.1 AA violations; tokens resolve correctly; no hardcoded colors visible.</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>

  <notes>
    Action key naming uses camelCase (`aiSummary`, `openFile`, `copyLink`, `openRecord`, `toggleWorkspace`, `pinToTop`) for TypeScript-friendly switch statements in consumer code. The first consumer is the Semantic Search PCF (FR-DOC-01) implemented in a later Phase 2 task; that task will provide the actual `onAction` switch that dispatches each action to its existing handler. Keep this component generic — no Semantic Search-specific behavior here. The portal gotcha is critical because MDA hosts often wrap the form in CSS that breaks default Menu portal mounting; the pattern document specifies the project-canonical mitigation.
  </notes>

